title: Reverse Integer
description: Given a signed 32-bit integer x, return x with its digits reversed. If reversing x causes the value to go outside the signed 32-bit integer range [-231, 231 - 1], then return 0.

title: Container With Most Water
description: You are given an integer array height of length n. There are n vertical lines drawn such that the two endpoints of the ith line are (i, 0) and (i, height[i]). Find two lines which, together with the x-axis, form a container that holds the most water.

title: Find the Duplicate Number
description: Given an array of integers nums containing n + 1 integers where each integer is in the range [1, n] inclusive, return the duplicate number.
constraint: Constraints: 1 <= n <= 105 nums.length == n + 1 1 <= nums[i] <= n All the integers in nums appear only once except for exactly one integer which appears twice.

title: Search in Rotated Sorted Array
description: Given an integer array nums sorted in ascending order (with distinct values), and given that nums is possibly rotated, search for a given target in nums and return its index. If not found, return -1.
constraint: Constraints: 1 <= nums.length <= 5000 -104 <= nums[i] <= 104 All values of nums are unique.

title: Product of Array Except Self
description: Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that answer[i] is equal to the product of all the elements of nums except nums[i]. The product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.
constraint: Constraints: 2 <= nums.length <= 105 -30 <= nums[i] <= 30 The product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.
